basics.name: Kailee Hung
basics.label: B.S. Computer Science | University of Hawaii at Manoa 2024

work.company: UH Manoa Information and Technology Services
work.summary: Contribute to the development of UI and API functionality on the UH Groupings project
highlights: Work in an agile project management environment using Java, JavaScript, HTML, and CSS
Transitioned into role of API Lead in January 2022 which involves management of the API side of the project, along with creating and distributing new tickets on JIRA
Assist in the creation of new features, optimizing code, fixing bugs, and increasing code coverage
Contribute to team documentation to aid future members
Participate in weekly meetings and code reviews
Mentor and onboard new team members

awards.title: Dean's List
awards.summary: Undergraduate students are awarded the Dean’s List distinction if they: (1) earn a semester grade point average of 3.5 or higher based on 12 credits or more taken for a grade, and (2) do not receive grades of W, I, F, or NC for that semester.

awards.title: Provost Achievement Scholarship
awards.summary: $40,000 scholarship distributed over 4 years at UH Manoa awarded to high-achieving Hawaii high school graduates and incoming freshman based on academics, leadership, and community service.

awards.title: Community Scholarship Fund
awards.summary: $2,625 scholarship for Hawaii residents to aid them in their academic journey.

awards.title: Summer Sophomore Merit Scholarship
awards.summary: $1,200 scholarship awarded to up to 75 UH Manoa students in recognition of their academic excellence.

awards.title: Stronger Together Hawaii Scholarship Fund
awards.summary: $3,500 scholarship awarded to selected students who participated in the Next Steps to Your Future program.

awards.title: AP Scholar with Honor
awards.summary: Granted to students who receive an average score of at least 3.25 on all AP Exams taken, and scores of 3 or higher on four or more of these exams.
